The end of the <span style="color: #D47B9B;">**USPD**</span> has left the more radical workers with two choices to vote on, and the <span style="color: #8B0000;">**KPD**</span> has capitalized on this opportunity. By agitating against the Republic for its inability to deal with the current hyperinflation crisis, much of the former <span style="color: #D47B9B;">**USPD**</span>’s voters look to the <span style="color: #8B0000;">**KPD**</span> as the only viable alternative to the more establishment-friendly <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span>. Interestingly, the <span style="color: #096300;">**DAP**</span> has also begun to rail against the Republic, blaming the detached liberal democracy and perceived abandonment of national pride and values for its current position. Most do not listen, but a few are lured by their slogans.

